Perry Ellis International Inc. (NASDAQ:PERY) Experiences Lighter than Average Trading Volume 












































 Finance DailyDaily markets, commodities, personal finance and economic newsPerry Ellis International Inc. (NASDAQ:PERY) Experiences Lighter than Average Trading Volume
July 25, 2017 By Ted Blackburn Tweet
        Advertisement



Trading volume for Perry Ellis International Inc. was 4,192 by the end of trading on Tuesday.  Trading volume was down 96.66% under the stocks average daily volume. 
 Here are a few additional firms who have increased or decreased their stake in (PERY).   As of quarter end Acadian Asset Management LLC had sold 68,583 shares trimming its stake by 33.9%. The value of the investment in Perry Ellis International Inc. decreased from $4,341,000 to $2,596,000 a change of 40.2% quarter to quarter. North Star Investment Management Corp. bolstered its ownership by buying 11,000 shares an increase of 14.4% in the quarter. North Star Investment Management Corp. claims 87,650 shares worth $1,706,000. The value of the position overall is up by 3.6%.
 Symphony Asset Management LLC augmented its position by buying 7,335 shares an increase of 39.8% as of 06/30/2016. Symphony Asset Management LLC now holds 25,782 shares with a value of $519,000. The total value of its holdings increased 13.1%. Morgan Stanley trimmed its holdings by selling 1,700 shares a decrease of 17.0%. Morgan Stanley controls 8,300 shares valued at $178,000. The value of the position overall is down by 28.5%.
  On June 1, 2016 Sidoti &amp; Co. added PERY to its research portfolio with an initial rating of “Buy”. On August 21 Wunderlich kept the company rating at “Buy” but raised the price target  to $35.00 from $31.00.        Advertisement






 August 20 investment analysts at Wunderlich left the stock rating at “Buy” and raised the price expectation from $31.00 to $35.00. On July 22 analysts at Brean Capital added the stock to its research portfolio setting a rating of “Buy” and setting a price target of $30.00.
 November 20 investment analysts at Wunderlich kept the stock rating at “Buy” but moved up the price target from $25.00 to $30.00. On November 11 the company was downgraded to “Hold” from “Buy” in a report from Standpoint Research.
 The company is trading up by 1.49% since yesterday’s close of $19.46.  The stock is trading at $19.75 a bit higher than $18.99, the stock’s 50 day moving average and which is marginally under the 200 day moving average of $21.01.  The 50 day moving average went up by +3.29% and the 200 day average went down by -6.66%. 
 The company’s P/E ratio is 23.32 and market cap is 294.31M.  As of the last earnings report the EPS was $0.84 and is estimated to be $2.13 for the current year with 15,008,000 shares currently outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is forecasted at $0.36 with next year’s EPS anticipated to be $2.34. 
 Perry Ellis International, Inc., launched on April 5, 1967, is an apparel company. The Company designs, sources, markets and licenses its products nationally and internationally at multiple price points and across all levels of retail distribution. The Company operates through four segments: Men’s Sportswear and Swim, Women’s Sportswear, Direct-to-Consumer and Licensing. The Business’s brands include Perry Ellis and Original Penguin by Munsingwear (Original Penguin), Ben Hogan, Cubavera, Farah, Grand Slam, Jantzen, Laundry by Shelli Segal, Rafaella and Savane..
        Advertisement




